Alastair Cook: New personnel gives England 'fresh' feeling
Media playback is not supported on this deviceAlastair Cook says the England camp feels "fresh and different" as theybegin life under new head coach Peter Moores.With assistant Paul Farbrace in tow, 51-year-old Moores begins his second period in charge with a one-day international against Scotland on Friday, almost five-and-a-half years his first spell in charge came to an end.Moores was dismissed as England coach in 2009 after a dispute with Kevin Pietersen, who isno longer part of the national set-up.